<h1 class="entry-title">COVID-19 Update: 3/31/20 7:30 p.m.</h1>
<p class="post-meta"> by <span class="author vcard"><a href="http://shasta.reddingschools.net/author/kmiller/" title="Posts by Kim Miller" rel="author">Kim Miller</a></span> | <span class="published">Mar 31, 2020</span> | <a href="http://shasta.reddingschools.net/category/miner-news/" rel="category tag">Miner News</a></p>
</div> 
<div class="entry-content">
<p><a href="http://shasta.reddingschools.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2020/03/Capture.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-15924" src="http://shasta.reddingschools.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2020/03/Capture-300x231.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="231" srcset="http://shasta.reddingschools.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2020/03/Capture-300x231.jpg 300w, http://shasta.reddingschools.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/13/2020/03/Capture.jpg 373w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px"></a></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Dear Shasta Elementary School Families,</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">I hope this letter finds you well.  We are currently experiencing an unprecedented event due to the state, national, and global pandemic.  When we started our closure, it was our plan to restart school after spring break. That plan is now on hold as the social distancing measures are still in place across California and Shasta County.  Shasta Elementary School is moving forward into distance learning activities to better serve your child. At this time, there is no end date that I can give you for our distance learning strategy, but it is still our hope that we will be able to welcome your children back to our schools before the end of the school year. This will be communicated more clearly as we learn more information going forward. Shasta Elementary School looks forward to the day that each and every child is back in school for face-to-face instruction. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Beginning the week of April 14th, each student will be issued a grade level learning packet. This packet will be collected at the end of each week and will be used by teachers to check students’ understanding of the assigned work.  The distribution and collection of learning packets will take place on a regularly scheduled day and time arranged on our campus. We will be sharing the exact pick up schedule soon, as we will still be following distancing practices for packet pick up and collection.  Expect this information before this Friday, April 3, 2020.  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Along with the learning packets, teachers are organizing a weekly schedule of communication with each student or groups of students. Teachers will be connecting with each family in order to collaborate and share the exact day(s) of the week and the time(s) the teacher will be supporting your child. In addition to these scheduled times, there will be a general office hour in which parents and students can reach out with any questions. This can be through email, ClassDojo, or other means set forth by your child’s teacher.  Be looking for this communication from your child’s teacher soon.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Together, we will navigate these uncharted waters. All of us at Shasta Elementary School  look forward to the day we can greet your children at our school doors with a smile to let them know that we missed them. If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to leave a message at the school.  Someone will get back to you as soon as possible.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Stay safe and be well,</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Robert Adams</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Superintendent </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Shasta Union Elementary School District</span></p>
</div> 
